The recommended way to install Frescobaldi (from the frescobaldi directory) is:


mkdir build	# (not needed when you use a release tarball)
cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$(kde4-config --exec-prefix)
make
make install

* If you install Frescobaldi from svn, you need LilyPond and ImageMagick to
  create the icons, and GNU Gettext to create the translations

* If you install Frescobaldi from a release tarball, the build directory already
  contains prebuilt icons and .mo files (translations)


Frescobaldi depends on:
  KDE4
  Qt >= 4.4
  Python >= 2.4
  PyQt4
  PyKDE4.
  lilypond-kde4 (from http://lilykde.googlecode.com/)

Other useful programs are:
  LilyPond (of course!) http://lilypond.org/
  Rumor                 http://www.volny.cz/smilauer/rumor/
  a MIDI player like timidity++, etc.
